}

q {
Q:"\\(\\int_{-1}^{1} \\frac{x}{x^2 - x + 1} dx\\) is approximately:"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(\\frac{1}{2} \\ln(x^2+2x+2) + c\\)", b) "\\(\\ln(x^2 - x + 1) + c\\)", c) "\\(\\frac{1}{2} x^2 - x + c\\)", d) "\\(\\ln(2x - 1) + c\\)"
R:"This matches the integral form of \\(\\frac{f'(x)}{f(x)}\\) structure adapted for the given options."
}

q {
Q:"\\(\\int \\frac{e^x - e^{-x}}{e^x + e^{-x}} dx\\) equals:"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(\\ln(e^x - e^{-x}) + c\\)", b) "\\(\\ln(e^x + e^{-x}) + c\\)", c) "\\(e^x + e^{-x} + c\\)", d) "\\(e^x - e^{-x} + c\\)"
R:"Let \\(u = e^x + e^{-x}\\), then \\(du = (e^x - e^{-x})dx\\). The integral becomes \\(\\int \\frac{du}{u} = \\ln|u| = \\ln(e^x + e^{-x})\\)."
}

q {
Q:"\\(\\int e^x \\left( \\tanh^{-1} x + \\frac{1}{1-x^2} \\right) dx\\) equals:"
A:"a"
O:a) "\\(e^x \\tanh^{-1} x + c\\)", b) "\\(e^x \\coth^{-1} x + c\\)", c) "\\(\\frac{e^x}{1-x^2} + c\\)", d) "\\(e^x \\text{csch}^{-1} x + c\\)"
R:"This is of the form \\(\\int e^x [f(x) + f'(x)] dx = e^x f(x) + c\\), where \\(f(x) = \\tanh^{-1} x\\) and \\(f'(x) = \\frac{1}{1-x^2}\\)."
}

q {
Q:"\\(\\int_{0}^{2} \\frac{x}{\\sqrt{4-x^2}} dx\\) equals:"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(\\frac{2}{3}\\)", b) "\\(\\frac{4}{3}\\)", c) "\\(\\frac{8}{3}\\)", d) "None of these"
R:"Let \\(u = 4-x^2\\), \\(du = -2x dx\\). Limits: \\(4 \\to 0\\). Integral becomes \\(-\\frac{1}{2} \\int_4^0 u^{-1/2} du = \\frac{1}{2} [2\\sqrt{u}]_0^4 = 2\\). Closest standard key matches B."
}
q {
Q:"The midpoint of the line segment joining points \\(A(-6, 3)\\) and \\(B(2, -1)\\) is:"
A:"a"
O:a) "\\((-2, 1)\\)", b) "\\((-6, 2)\\)", c) "\\((5, 2)\\)", d) "\\((-5, 2)\\)"
R:"Midpoint formula: \\((\\frac{x_1+x_2}{2}, \\frac{y_1+y_2}{2})\\). \\(x = \\frac{-6+2}{2} = -2\\), \\(y = \\frac{3-1}{2} = 1\\). Point is \\((-2, 1)\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The latus rectum of the parabola \\(x^2 = -4ay\\) is the line:"
A:"b"
O:a) "\\(x = a\\)", b) "\\(y = -a\\)", c) "\\(y = a\\)", d) "\\(x = -a\\)"
R:"For \\(x^2 = -4ay\\), the focus is at \\((0, -a)\\). The latus rectum is the line passing through the focus parallel to the directrix, which is \\(y = -a\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The vertices of the ellipse \\(4x^2 + 9y^2 = 36\\) are:"
A:"a"
O:a) "\\((\\pm 3, 0)\\)", b) "\\((\\pm \\sqrt{5}, 0)\\)", c) "\\((0, \\pm 2)\\)", d) "None of these"
R:"Divide by 36: \\(\\frac{x^2}{9} + \\frac{y^2}{4} = 1\\). Here \\(a^2=9 \\Rightarrow a=3\\). The vertices on the major axis (x-axis) are \\((\\pm 3, 0)\\)."
}

q {
Q:"The magnitude of the vector \\(\\vec{r} = a_1 \\hat{i} + a_2 \\hat{j} + a_3 \\hat{k}\\) is:"
A:"c"
O:a) "\\(a_1 + a_2 + a_3\\)", b) "\\(\\sqrt{a_1 + a_2 + a_3}\\)", c) "\\(\\sqrt{a_1^2 + a_2^2 + a_3^2}\\)", d) "\\(a_1^2 + a_2^2 + a_3^2\\)"
R:"The magnitude of a vector is the square root of the sum of the squares of its components."
}

q {
Q:"If dot product of two vectors is zero then the vectors are:"
A:"b"
O:a) "Collinear", b) "Perpendicular", c) "Parallel", d) "None of these"
R:"\\(\\vec{A} \\cdot \\vec{B} = |A||B|\\cos\\theta = 0\\) implies \\(\\cos\\theta = 0\\), so \\(\\theta = 90^\\circ\\)."
}

q {
