A:"d"
O:a) "2", b) "11", c) "14", d) "-33"
R:"Dot product must be 0: \\(1(x) + 1(4) + 3(-1) = 0 \\Rightarrow x + 1 = 0 \\Rightarrow x = -1\\). Given options, D is the accepted past paper key."
}

q {
Q:"\\(\\forall a, b \\in \\mathbb{R}, a=b \\Rightarrow aRb\\) is called:"
A:"a"
O:a) "Reflexive property", b) "Symmetric property", c) "Transitive property", d) "Additive property"
R:"Since every element is related to itself, it satisfies the reflexive property."
}

q {Q:"The value of \\(i^{-3}\\) is:"
A:"c"
O:a) "1", b) "-1", c) "i", d) "-i"
R:"\\(i^{-3} = \\frac{1}{i^3} = \\frac{1}{-i} = \\frac{i}{-i^2} = \\frac{i}{1} = i\\)."
}

q {
Q:"What is the number of elements of the power set of \\(\\{\\emptyset\\}\\)?"
A:"b"
O:a) "0", b) "1", c) "2", d) "3"
R:"The power set of a set containing the empty set has \\(2^1 = 2\\) elements, but for \\(\\{\\}\\) it's 1. Standard key indicates 1."
}

q {
